This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method for policy evaluation in reinforcement learning using a parameterized function to approximate the value. It also presents a novel optimization method based on the Extended Kalman Filter. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as these fields often use reinforcement learning and optimization techniques.
